# Python conventions

- FastAPI routers stay thin; business logic in `app/services/`
- Pydantic models in `app/models/` for all request/response shapes
- Settings via `app/config.py` / pydantic-settings — never read env ad hoc in services
- Async HTTP for OSINT clients; sync OK for header parsing and CLI
- Canary storage: `app/services/canary/storage.py`; validate tokens before logging hits
- Protected routes: use existing API key dependency — don't bypass in production paths
- Errors exposed to clients must be sanitized; details in server logs only
- New CLI modules under `app/cli/`; wire scripts in `scripts/` for Make/deploy use
